  "prompt": "What are the best small classes for freshmen at Hawaii Pacific University?",
  "response": "At Hawaii Pacific University, small class sizes are a hallmark of the educational experience, allowing for personalized attention and faculty interaction. While I can't provide a specific list of classes as offerings change each semester, here are some general recommendations for small classes that are often well-regarded by freshmen:\n\n1. **Introduction to Psychology** - This foundational course typically attracts a lot of interest and encourages interactive discussions.\n  \n2. **First-Year Seminar** - Many universities offer first-year seminars designed to help students transition into college, covering various topics and often featuring small class sizes.\n\n3. **Composition or English 101** - Freshman writing classes generally have fewer students, allowing for more feedback on writing skills.\n\n4. **Introduction to Environmental Science** - Given Hawaii's unique ecology, these classes can be particularly engaging and often keep enrollment numbers low.\n\n5. **Foreign Language Courses** - Beginner language classes often have smaller sizes, providing a more immersive learning experience.\n\n6. **Art or Music Classes** - Introductory classes in the arts often feature a hands-on learning approach with smaller groups.\n\nTo find the best options, check the university course catalog, speak with an academic advisor, or reach out to professors in your areas of interest. This will provide the latest information on class sizes and help you identify courses that align with your academic goals.",
